    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1385"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1385">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.0067/6</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 7, 12.25 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>911. Yesterday Italian and Russian interests at Smyrna were turned over to our
                    Consul. Interests of Italy, Russia, and Montenegro everywhere in the Empire
                    except at Constantinople are now in our charge. There are no officials here that
                    can be spared to take charge of Adrianople and Brusa. Can you send me some for
                    that purpose? There are no Americans at Adrianople and the two at Brusa are
                    unsuitable for the purpose.</p>
                <p>Italian subjects have been prevented from leaving Mersina, Alexandretta, and
                    elsewhere. Italian Ambassador gave Ottoman Government <pb facs="1235" n="977"
                        xml:id="pg_977"/> ultimatum expiring to-day to permit these departures.
                    Turkish Government has yielded on all points and I am now requesting <hi
                        rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Caesar</hi> to call at
                    Mersina, Alexandretta, and also at Sighajik, to transport the Smyrna Italians to
                    Rhodes. Inform Italian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
